This paper deals with scheduling and rate adaptation in wireless networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves channel estimation and statistics, which are related to information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also proposes a joint learning and scheduling policy, which involves optimization and decision-making, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. The paper also involves probabilistic modeling and analysis, which is related to machine learning and statistics, making cs.MA (Machine Learning) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves optimization and decision-making, which is related to reinforcement learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible category.
